'''A K M Shafiqur Rahman'''<ref name=chat/> (known as '''Shafiq Tuhin'''; born 27 September 1975)<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.priyo.com/people/shafiq-tuhin-201825/|title=শফিক তুহিন|accessdate=2018-06-07}}</ref> is a Bangladeshi lyricist, music director and singer. As of 2012, he wrote about 1,000 songs.<ref name=music/> He earned the [[Bangladesh National Film Award for Best Lyrics]] for the song ''Choto Choto Golpo''<ref name=chat/> in the film ''[[Projapoti]]'' (2011) and Citycell-Channel-I Music Award in 2006, 2011 and 2013.<ref name=award>{{cite news|url=http://oldsite.dailyjanakantha.com/news_view.php?nc=42&dd=2013-11-25&ni=155606|title=পুরস্কার পেলে কার ভাল না লাগে ॥ শফিক তুহিন|newspaper=Daily Janakantha|date=2013-11-25|accessdate=2018-06-07|language=bn|trans-title=Who doesn't like to win an award - Shafiq Tuhin}}</ref>

==Background and career==
Tuhin started writing lyrics in 1995. His first written song was sung by singer [[Shakila Zafar]].<ref name=music/> In 2001, just after graduating from the [[University of Dhaka]], he chose lyric writing as his career.<ref name=music/> 

Tuhin has written songs for other singers including [[Sabina Yasmin]], [[Runa Laila]], [[Shahnaz Rahmatullah]], [[Tapan Chowdhury]] and [[Kumar Bishwajit]].<ref name=music/>

In 2012, Tuhin debuted in composing tune and lyrics for films through ''Onnorokom Bhalobasha''.<ref name=chat>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thedailystar.net/showbiz/grapevine/chat-shafiq-tuhin-1237768|title=A Chat With Shafiq Tuhin|date=2016-06-11|work=The Daily Star|access-date=2018-06-07|language=en|author=Zahid Akbar}}</ref>

